    stable 2.0.1 2.0.0 1.0.3 1.0.2 1.0.1 1.0.0
   require guile lame libgnomeui
  optional alsa-lib  '' --disable-alsatest with ALSA audio output support
  optional libmad    '' ''                 to enable mp3 import and export
  optional libvorbis '' ''                 for ogg vorbis decoding

    ignore 'rc'
  category audio/editor
 attribute gnome
    source glame/glame-$VERSION.tar.gz
       url "$SOURCEFORGE_URL"
  homepage http://glame.sourceforge.net
  estimate 500
      desc 'glame (GNU/Linux Audio Mechanics) is ment to be the gimp of audio processing.
It is designed to be a powerful, fast, stable, and easily
extensible sound editor for Linux and compatible systems.
It has full support for non-destructive editing including
undo/redo and applying LADSPA effects.'
